    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="811"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/754½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Lend-Lease Administrator</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Burns</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-18">November 18,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Acheson</hi>: As you know, the President, on
                    November 7, 1941, found the defense of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics
                    vital to the defense of the United States. Pursuant to this finding, I am
                    arranging to have defense articles transferred to the Soviet Government as
                    quickly as possible.</p>
                <p>The Soviet Government has already filed the necessary papers under Sections 4 and
                    7 of the Lend-Lease Act. It might be advisable, however, to obtain a formal
                    master agreement embodying the substance of the exchange of notes between the
                    President and Premier Stalin, the representations under Sections 4 and 7 of the
                    Lend-Lease Act and any other provisions deemed necessary or desirable.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Burns</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
